<p>
Of course, in  <xref ref="EXAMPLEexamp:DiffRulesInConcert2"></xref> we could have multiplied the
factors together before differentiating and obtained the same
answer:
<md>
<mrow>
  \dx((2x+5)(3x-7)) \amp = \dx(6x^2+x-35)
</mrow>
<mrow>
  \amp = 6(2x\dx{x})+\dx{x}-0
</mrow>
<mrow>
  \amp = (12x+1)\dx{x}.
</mrow>
</md>
Either procedure will work. You are at liberty to do whichever you
prefer.
</p>
